Using your knowledge of medical conditions, can you determine the cause of a set of rare symptoms that are often misdiagnosed? Below is a list of symptoms that can indicate a variety of illnesses. Your task is to use your deductive skills to determine which illness is causing the symptoms:
| Illness | Symptoms |
|---------|----------|
| Guillain-Barre Syndrome | muscle weakness, tingling or numbness in the hands and feet, difficulty breathing |
| Myasthenia Gravis | muscle weakness, difficulty speaking or swallowing, drooping eyelids |
| Multiple Sclerosis | numbness or tingling in the limbs, difficulty walking or maintaining balance, blurred vision |
In addition, here is a code snippet that may assist you in your deduction:
```
if (muscleWeakness && tinglingOrNumbness && difficultyBreathing) {
  console.log("You may have Guillain-Barre Syndrome");
} else if (muscleWeakness && (difficultySpeakingOrSwallowing || droopingEyelids)) {
  console.log("You may have Myasthenia Gravis");
} else if ((numbnessOrTingling || difficultyWalking) && blurredVision) {
  console.log("You may have Multiple Sclerosis");
} else {
  console.log("Your symptoms do not appear to match any of these illnesses");
}
```
